<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1451,1958,2057]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,201,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[209,234,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zahlbruckner, A." box="[234,466,1958,1984]" firstAuthor="Zahlbruckner" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l ' Herbier Boissier" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="445 - 460" part="7" refId="ref8621" refString="Zahlbruckner, A. (1907) Plantae Paraguarienses novae vel minus cognitae. Bulletin de l ' Herbier Boissier, ser. 2, 7: 445 - 460." title="Plantae Paraguarienses novae vel minus cognitae" type="journal article" year="1907">Zahlbruckner (1907)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zahlbruckner" authorityYear="1907" box="[587,769,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hassleri">
<emphasis box="[587,769,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lobelia hassleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the specimen 
<emphasis box="[1034,1184,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Hassler 8970</emphasis>
, collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[1334,1447,1958,1984]" country="Paraguay" name="Caaguazu" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Caaguazú</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,242,1995,2021]" name="Paraguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
. Amongst the various 
<typeStatus box="[507,608,1995,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">syntypes</typeStatus>
, the sheets housed at G under the numbers [00106161] and [00106162] clearly constitute a single specimen, with complete original labels in Zahlbruckner’s hand and perfectly fitting the original description. Based on Art. 8.2 of ICN (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J." box="[673,836,158,184]" firstAuthor="McNeill" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="1112 - 1113" part="63" refId="ref7546" refString="McNeill, J. (2014) Holotype specimens and type citations: General issues. Taxon 63: 1112 - 1113. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 635.7" title="Holotype specimens and type citations: General issues" type="journal article" year="2014">McNeill 2014</bibRefCitation>
), these plant fragments are thus considered as a single specimen mounted on two sheets and are here selected as the 
<typeStatus box="[826,932,194,220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
